=Description
The [[SyntaxHighlighterRubyPlugin|https://github.com/GBognar/SyntaxHighlighterPlugin]]  is a [[TiddlyWiki|http://www.tiddlywiki.com]] plugin which enables you to syntax highlight Ruby, CSS, XML/HTML and JavaScript content in your ~TiddlyWiki.

It is built on PMario's [[SyntaxHighlighterPlugin|https://github.com/pmario/SyntaxHighlighterPlugin]], which uses Alex Gorbatchev 's [[SyntaxHighlighter|http://alexgorbatchev.com/SyntaxHighlighter/]].

=Current Development
The current development focuses on providing a //really **fast** and **comfortable**// solution to syntax highlight Ruby code in TiddlyWiki.

=The 'SyntaxHighlighterPluginFacelift' branch
The [[SyntaxHighlighterPluginFacelift branch|https://github.com/GBognar/SyntaxHighlighterPlugin/tree/SyntaxHighlighterPluginFacelift]] contains a version of
PMario's original [[SyntaxHighlighterPlugin|https://github.com/pmario/SyntaxHighlighterPlugin]] with minor modifications, namely:
* more verbose description in the documentation of the plugin,
* less verbose description in the plugin itself and
* some minor changes to the styles governing the appearance of highlighted content.